sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client<br/>(KServe / ModelMesh)
    participant Router as Router (Rust)<br/>8033/TCP gRPC<br/>Optional TLS/mTLS
    participant Queue as Validation + Queue<br/>Continuous Batcher
    participant Shard0 as Python Shard 0<br/>Unix Socket gRPC
    participant ShardN as Python Shard 1..N<br/>Unix Socket gRPC
    participant GPU as NVIDIA GPU<br/>CUDA 12.1

    Note over Client,GPU: Flow 1: Text Generation Request
    Client->>Router: gRPC Generate/GenerateStream<br/>Port 8033/TCP<br/>Optional TLS + mTLS
    Router->>Queue: Validate request params<br/>(max tokens, temperature, etc.)
    Queue->>Shard0: Prefill batch (gRPC)<br/>Unix Socket, plaintext
    Shard0->>GPU: Forward pass (PyTorch/CUDA)
    GPU-->>Shard0: First token logits
    Shard0-->>Queue: Prefill result + first token

    loop Auto-regressive decoding
        Queue->>Shard0: NextToken (gRPC)<br/>Unix Socket, plaintext
        Shard0->>GPU: Decode step
        GPU-->>Shard0: Next token logits
        Shard0-->>Queue: Generated token
    end

    Queue-->>Router: Complete response / stream chunks
    Router-->>Client: gRPC response<br/>Optional TLS

    Note over Client,GPU: Flow 2: Health Check
    participant Kubelet as Kubelet
    Kubelet->>Router: GET /health<br/>Port 3000/TCP HTTP plaintext
    Router->>Shard0: Health RPC<br/>Unix Socket gRPC
    Shard0-->>Router: Health OK
    Router-->>Kubelet: 200 OK

    Note over Client,GPU: Flow 3: Tensor Parallel (Multi-GPU)
    Note over Shard0,ShardN: Launcher spawns N shards<br/>(one per GPU)
    Shard0->>ShardN: PyTorch Distributed init<br/>Port 29500/TCP master_port
    Shard0->>ShardN: NCCL AllReduce<br/>Shared Memory (/dev/shm)
    ShardN-->>Shard0: Synchronized tensor results
